Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Dohyun Park

My meme

#launch MAGICK library
library(magick)

#studio picture
studio <- image_read(path = 'images/mixing_studio.jpeg') %>%
  image_scale(500)

#earphone picture
earphone <- image_read(path = 'images/broken_earphone.jpg') %>%
  image_scale(500)

#studio text
studio_text <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                          height = 500, 
                          color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Where the artist \nmake their music",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

#earphone text
earphone_text <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Earphone that I use \nwhen listening to \nmy favourite \nartist's music",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

#top row
top_row <- c(earphone, earphone_text) %>%
  image_append()

#bottom row
bottom_row <- c(studio, studio_text) %>%
  image_append()

#merging top and bottom row
meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(800)

#writing the final meme image
image_write(meme, path = 'my_meme.png', format = 'png')

I wanted to make a meme that audio engineers can relate

My animation

#launch MAGICK library
library(magick)

#elements in my animation
left_elmo <- image_read("images/elmo.png") %>%
  image_scale(500)

right_elmo <- image_flop(left_elmo) %>%
  image_scale(500)

#frames for my animation
frame1 <- image_blur(left_elmo,10,5)

frame2 <- image_blur(right_elmo,10,5)

frame3 <- left_elmo

frame4 <- right_elmo

frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 2)

image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
